  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0ba8\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b87\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0b9e\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc0\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A youth who commented on a Facebook post was arrested under the Emergency Act - remanded in custody",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "A suspect has been arrested on charges of sharing a Facebook post expressing support for the People's Liberation Movement and making malicious comments against the police and security forces on the post.",
        "The police said that the 28-year-old Ahmed Niswar, who hails from Ghali, Fort area, was arrested by the officers of the Southern Provincial Sub-Division of the Computer Crime Division of the Criminal Investigation Department.",
        "In this situation, the suspect was produced before Galli Magistrate Pavitra Sanjivani Pathirana yesterday (25) and the judge has ordered him to be remanded until August 8.",
        "CIT stated that the suspect has committed an offense under Section 15 of the Gazette Notification No. 2289/07 containing the provisions of Emergency Laws published on July 18, and that he has committed crimes under the Penal Code and Computer Crime Acts. The authorities produced the person in court.",
        "Commenting on the arrest to the media, Police Spokesperson Senior Superintendent of Police Nihal Talduwa said that the suspect was arrested based on two comments he had made on a Facebook post.",
        "One of them is 'On the next 9th, there will be a riot across the country. In it, the police and soldiers along with their families will be treated like dogs (killed) at every place and on the roads. People from Jaffna, I have talked to Tamils \u200b\u200bI know and invited two trains full of people. If I alone can do this, what cannot be done if all the people of the country come together.' He said that there was, and the other comment continues, 'Kaki dogs and Khema Pingbios told Ranil........'.",
        "The Police Spokesman mentioned that investigations are underway to arrest the person who uploaded the main post in which the comments were posted on Facebook, and those who expressed interest in these comments."
      ],
